.TH "pvrdma_reg_user_mr" 9 "pvrdma_reg_user_mr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pvrdma_reg_user_mr \- register a userspace memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_mr *" pvrdma_reg_user_mr
.BI "(struct ib_pd *pd "  ","
.BI "u64 start "  ","
.BI "u64 length "  ","
.BI "u64 virt_addr "  ","
.BI "int access_flags "  ","
.BI "struct ib_udata *udata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pd" 12
protection domain
.IP "start" 12
starting address
.IP "length" 12
length of region
.IP "virt_addr" 12
I/O virtual address
.IP "access_flags" 12
access flags for memory region
.IP "udata" 12
user data
.SH "RETURN"
ib_mr pointer on success, otherwise returns an errno.
